00:56:02.496 --> 00:56:03.496
Ju Ah.

00:56:04.806 --> 00:56:07.306
- How was your workshop? - It was fine.

00:56:07.766 --> 00:56:09.276
What are you watching, Uncle?

00:56:10.076 --> 00:56:11.306
Just flipping through channels.

00:56:12.506 --> 00:56:14.746
- Can I have a beer? - Of course.

00:56:16.876 --> 00:56:19.516
This is nice. Here, cheers.

00:56:20.586 --> 00:56:21.586
Cheers.

00:56:24.786 --> 00:56:26.256
Goodness.

00:56:32.896 --> 00:56:34.466
Uncle...

00:56:56.686 --> 00:56:58.556
Gong Jeong Han, that jerk.

00:57:00.556 --> 00:57:01.896
Are you that upset, honey?

00:57:02.696 --> 00:57:04.456
Ever since we were kids, they always compared us.

00:57:05.226 --> 00:57:07.126
It was always, "Jeong Han this, Jeong Han that."

00:57:08.066 --> 00:57:10.666
But still. How could he not vote for me?

00:57:12.436 --> 00:57:13.506
Honey.

00:57:18.646 --> 00:57:19.806
This is really depressing.

00:57:36.596 --> 00:57:39.166
Grandpa, you really went too far this time.

00:57:39.826 --> 00:57:42.636
Exactly, Dad. After seeing how hard he worked,

00:57:42.836 --> 00:57:44.066
how could you vote for the other guy?

00:57:45.536 --> 00:57:50.136
Dad's so petty, he'll sulk forever. He's even skipping breakfast.

00:57:53.646 --> 00:57:55.346
You all can go ahead and eat.

00:57:55.846 --> 00:57:57.376
I don't really have an appetite either.

00:57:58.716 --> 00:58:00.386
It was all for Dong Ik's sake.

00:58:02.256 --> 00:58:05.286
Jeong Han has no political ambition,

00:58:05.626 --> 00:58:07.626
so he would do a proper job.

00:58:08.226 --> 00:58:09.226
Dong Ik, on the other hand...

00:58:10.126 --> 00:58:13.726
His only goal was getting elected, so he would've ignored his duties.

00:58:14.396 --> 00:58:16.366
I guess you're right.

00:58:16.836 --> 00:58:19.966
If that happened, he would've lost his run for council.

00:58:20.706 --> 00:58:24.576
He must win people over for votes, just like he's doing now.

00:58:25.606 --> 00:58:29.616
You're absolutely right, Father. Then please, enjoy the food.

00:58:31.176 --> 00:58:32.246
How much do you want?

00:58:35.586 --> 00:58:38.226
I'll give it to you as an apology.

00:58:39.256 --> 00:58:41.256
How much will it take to make things right?

00:58:44.256 --> 00:58:46.066
Forty thousand dollars, Father.

00:58:49.796 --> 00:58:50.796
Done.

00:58:57.636 --> 00:58:58.706
Forty thousand?

00:59:06.886 --> 00:59:09.755
Dad always takes your side.

00:59:09.756 --> 00:59:11.486
Forty thousand dollars, just like that.

00:59:11.886 --> 00:59:14.256
Isn't this what they call a blessing in disguise?

00:59:14.586 --> 00:59:16.396
Such is life.

00:59:17.626 --> 00:59:21.996
I'm going to get ready. Could you do the dishes first?

00:59:22.066 --> 00:59:24.666
Of course. You think I'd only do the dishes?

00:59:24.866 --> 00:59:27.736
I'll do anything. Where are you off to?

00:59:28.206 --> 00:59:31.776
A lady I met in a class at the community center told me...

00:59:32.006 --> 00:59:35.946
about a private detective agency great for finding runaway husbands.

00:59:36.376 --> 00:59:37.576
A private detective agency?

00:59:39.216 --> 00:59:43.756
- A lawyer? - Yes. I know a family lawyer.

00:59:44.186 --> 00:59:46.686
I'm going to go talk to them about our realistic options.

00:59:47.386 --> 00:59:48.926
Okay.

00:59:50.496 --> 00:59:51.766
I thought you were heading out today.

00:59:52.996 --> 00:59:55.196
I'm just going to buy some supplies for the pharmacy before I go.

00:59:56.066 --> 00:59:57.566
By the way, about this laptop...

00:59:58.136 --> 00:59:59.766
Aunt used this sometimes too, right?

01:00:00.136 --> 01:00:02.936
Yes, she did. Why?

01:00:03.076 --> 01:00:05.946
It's automatically logged in to a web portal with her email.

01:00:06.446 --> 01:00:07.446
- What? - What?

01:00:10.416 --> 01:00:14.086
I thought it was my account, but it has a new order and address.

01:00:28.026 --> 01:00:29.966
Wait, Cabanel?

01:00:30.696 --> 01:00:33.836
Cabanel. It's Cabanel. Cabanel... Stepmom.

01:00:36.076 --> 01:00:37.876
Stepmom!

01:00:38.976 --> 01:00:41.406
- The Cabanel bag's been listed. - What?

01:00:41.446 --> 01:00:45.016
I think Uncle listed it on a resale app to sell it!

01:00:45.816 --> 01:00:49.716
- Really? - Yes, really! Where's Aunt?

01:00:51.016 --> 01:00:52.256
Excuse me, Chief.

01:00:53.886 --> 01:00:58.296
By any chance, can you do location or vehicle tracking?

01:00:58.366 --> 01:00:59.826
(Warm and Reliable Police)

01:00:59.896 --> 01:01:04.296
That's a hot request these days. Location and vehicle tracking.

01:01:06.066 --> 01:01:07.706
Is this about a family member?

01:01:08.236 --> 01:01:12.406
If you file a missing person report, we can help you with that.

01:01:13.006 --> 01:01:14.076
No, it's not like that.

01:01:15.376 --> 01:01:18.816
I couldn't just sit around, so I thought I'd come and ask.

01:01:19.916 --> 01:01:21.286
- I see. - Right.

01:01:28.656 --> 01:01:29.796
Excuse me.

01:01:29.956 --> 01:01:33.496
Can't you just run the license plate through the system?

01:01:34.926 --> 01:01:37.266
- Can't you do it for me? - I can't do that.

01:01:41.606 --> 01:01:43.606
- Please, sir. I'm begging you. - What?

01:01:43.936 --> 01:01:48.516
Can't you just find out where he is? The plate is 314 J9542.

01:01:48.776 --> 01:01:50.516
- I can't. - Wait, 314 J9542?

01:01:50.576 --> 01:01:52.716
- Chief, please. Just this once. - We can't.

01:01:52.786 --> 01:01:57.656
- Chief, please. Just once... - Auntie! I know where Uncle is!

01:01:57.816 --> 01:02:01.526
- What? - That Cabanel bag! For real! Hurry!

01:02:02.226 --> 01:02:03.826
- Where is he? - Quick!

01:02:03.896 --> 01:02:06.866
- Chief? - What?

01:02:07.396 --> 01:02:08.536
The person that lady is looking for...

01:02:09.066 --> 01:02:10.136
I think it's this guy.

01:02:12.006 --> 01:02:13.006
What?

01:02:19.176 --> 01:02:21.406
Mom, I think that's the place.

01:02:25.546 --> 01:02:28.386
(Hui Gyeong Hair Salon)

01:02:35.396 --> 01:02:36.796
(Hui Gyeong Hair Salon)

01:02:37.796 --> 01:02:39.326
Hurry up and come out, honey.

01:02:42.396 --> 01:02:43.436
That's Hui Gyeong.

01:02:47.306 --> 01:02:48.976
Honey, just a second.

01:02:49.936 --> 01:02:51.906
(Hui Gyeong Hair Salon)

01:02:52.046 --> 01:02:53.746
Hey, that guy.

01:02:55.346 --> 01:02:57.646
Oh, my. Wait.

01:02:58.116 --> 01:02:59.716
Isn't he the son-in-law from the Korean medicine clinic?

01:03:00.646 --> 01:03:01.646
No way.

01:03:02.216 --> 01:03:04.086
- Honey, wait just a second. - Okay.

01:03:05.956 --> 01:03:07.726
- Mom, Grandma. - I can't believe it.

01:03:08.326 --> 01:03:09.326
What is it?

01:03:10.526 --> 01:03:11.526
Look.

01:03:15.296 --> 01:03:17.696
- This is it, right? - Dong Suk, over here!

01:03:20.566 --> 01:03:23.406
- What now? - If you go this way...

01:03:23.876 --> 01:03:24.876
It's close by.

01:03:52.966 --> 01:03:55.806
(Recipe for Love)

01:03:56.706 --> 01:03:57.936
Are you protesting or something?

01:03:58.806 --> 01:04:02.216
- Gong Ju Ah and I are just friends. - Friends?

01:04:02.276 --> 01:04:03.276
We're old friends.

01:04:03.346 --> 01:04:05.846
Then why the long face? Are you sure you're just friends?

01:04:05.916 --> 01:04:07.546
Men and women can't be just friends.

01:04:07.646 --> 01:04:08.656
Well...

01:04:08.986 --> 01:04:10.556
What about my place?

01:04:10.886 --> 01:04:14.886
But apparently, their parents have also been my patients.

01:04:15.156 --> 01:04:16.195
I wonder who they are.

01:04:16.196 --> 01:04:18.126
How about a blind date with my brother?

01:04:19.066 --> 01:04:20.166
A blind date?

01:04:20.896 --> 01:04:23.235
We truly love each other.

01:04:23.236 --> 01:04:25.505
Loving someone's no crime, is it?

01:04:25.506 --> 01:04:26.506
Hey!